      "content": "While applying ointment and doing warm compresses can be helpful, it's not a substitute for professional medical evaluation and treatment. Not seeing a doctor when necessary can lead to delayed healing, potential complications, and even scarring. Applying a thick layer of ointment may actually trap bacteria underneath the dressing, worsening the infection, so it's best to wait for an appointment or advise the surgery to reschedule for a more convenient time.",
